<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1915-11-27T10:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1915-11-27T10:00:00-05:00" n="102" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d102">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72119/90</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Italy</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_PTN1" type="from"><hi rend="italic">Page</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Rome</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-11-27T16:00:00+01:00">
                                    <hi rend="italic">November 27, 1915, 4 p. m.</hi>
                                </date>
                                <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received 8 p. m.</hi>]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>464. Reported Germany will, on overrunning Servia, probably within few
                            days, make proposals peace, she demanding control Belgium, Poland,
                            Servia, and have large indemnity, while Bulgaria realizes aspirations
                            Macedonia. Cardinal Hartmann’s visit to Pope rumored to have reference
                            to this.</p>
                        <p>Italy is expected to send army to Albania, but report is she asks
                            cooperation other Allies.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <persName corresp="#p_PTN1">
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Nelson Page</hi>
                                </persName>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>